  <static seed="606" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/PolynomialMultiplication/PolynomialMultiplication75.pg">
    <statement><p>Multiply the polynomials.</p>
<p><m>\left({5x-6}\right)\left({x+3}\right)=</m><fillin characters="32" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>5x^{2}+9x-18</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>We use the FOIL technique: <alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast. <me>\begin{aligned}
              \left({5x-6}\right)({x+3})\amp ={5x^{2}+15x-6x-18}\\
                                \amp ={5x^{2}+9x-18}
      \end{aligned}</me></p>
</solution>
